,Recommended,269230,8978031,"Posted: 4 February, 2014",all,Trynant,"I playtested this, bought it on Humble Store, and now am playing and loving Aces Wild on Steam. Since its Humble Store release I've spent dozens and dozens of hours playing, and my time with this game is far from over.The controls are easy to pickup but are incredibly precise. You can do crazy combos and fly around the screen with your aerial-powered fighter using a minimal amount of buttons.The game is challenging but fair. Cliche statement, yes, but true in the case of Aces Wild. Nothing that the game throws at you is outside is unbeatable if you've got the skill.Do you want a score-attack focused game without those annoying unlockables or DLC? All the content in Aces Wild is available to play from the get go. Do you want to jump straight to the final boss on hardest difficulty? Go for it! It's all good!Lastly, and possibly what Aces Wild does best, is how much you can simply improve playing the game and how rewarding that feels. The skill ceiling in Aces Wild is absurdly high, and playing through the five difficulties gives a gradual learning curve instead of creating brick walls to bash your head on. Soon enough you'll be flying through dozens if not hundreds of attacks each minute, crashing your fists/swords against enemies so hard *it kills everything nearby*In short, this game is incredibly challenging, incredibly deep, and incredibly great. GO WILD!!"
,Recommended,269230,30777719,Posted: 27 March,all,ErbanVision,Aces Wild: Manic Brawling Action! is an interested game filed with chaotic action.There isn't much of a story other than win and defeat everyone.At first i was not enjoying Ace Wild i felt that it was unbalanced. However when i discover that you could doge attack than it became more about skill. So i started enjoy the challenge that the game had to offerUnfortunately the game is kinda simplistic in its design and once you have seen all the level that the game has to offer the chances are that you will not comme back to play this game again.There also is not much variety in the enemy types it does not hinder the experience but more would of been appreciated. Boss are hard and punishing but there is a fun factor in defeating them. One of the high points of Ace Wild is the retro soundtrack. It's really good and puts the player in the mood to destroy your enemy.Sadly Ace Wild is a really short Game my first run of the game took me 1h30 to completed it.In 2017 Ace Wild suffers from big optimisation problem with windows 10 and with the Steam ControllerThe steam controller will crash the game and to get this game working you will need to set Ace Wild in compatibility mode Windows Xp or Windows 7. But with that said the steam page does inform the consumer that this game was optimised for Windows Xp so i would not blame the dev for that.7.5/10 Verdict: There is some fun to be had with Ace Wild but the game has aged in it's 4 year that it was released on Steam. Since then so many other indie games have released and the optimisation problems that it has grown to have make it hard to recommend at a full price purchase.
