76561198078317925,Recommended,269230,22318041,"Posted: 9 April, 2016",all,IN OPTIONS,"Its an easy to get into beat em up. Rather than complex combos, you really just have one combo that you mash over and over, but doing this builds your potential to do more damage over time as well as cash it out for gigantic burst damage. The dodge mechanic is nice for the bullet hell style gameplay, and you cant just spam dodge to win, which is nice. Yeah, an over the top bullet hell beat em up, that pretty much sums up how fun this sounds. Again, Its really easy to get into, and even harder to not crack a smile while playing. The soundtrack is chiptune, which may or may not be your taste. But as someone who can enjoy chiptune, I thought the soundtrack was pretty solid. For a traditional art style, the animations are very smooth and match the hitboxes of your attacks very well. My ONLY complaint is that my favorite playable character is a reskin of a common enemy, and that can lead to losing track of where you are while playing him; However, you can change the palette, which helps quite a bit with that.TL;DRits a gud one, a hidden gem, even. ESPECIALLY for 10 bucks."
